<p>The <code>left</code> function returns the first N characters of a string.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | left(10){close}</pre>
<p>First 10: <b>{echo $sampleText | left(10)}</b></p>

<h2>Abbreviation</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'Documentation' | left(3){close}</pre>
<p>Abbrev: <b>{echo 'Documentation' | left(3)}</b></p>

<h2>Initial</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'John' | left(1){close}</pre>
<p>Initial: <b>{echo 'John' | left(1)}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | left(20) | upper{close}</pre>
<p>First 20 uppercase: <b>{echo $sampleText | left(20) | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo $email | before('@') | left(5) | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Username prefix: <b>{echo $email | before('@') | left(5) | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'Hello World' | left(5) | trim{close}</pre>
<p>Trimmed left: <b>{echo 'Hello World' | left(5) | trim}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>If the string is shorter than N, the entire string is returned.</p>
